    Class Description
    Animal
    The Class Animal is responsible for holding all the information necessary for the specific animal.
    Animal.AgeCategory
    The Enum AgeCategory that holds the different age categories for the animals
    Animal.Size
    The Enum Size for different sizes of animals
    ArrayListQueue<E>
    The Class ArrayListQueue will be used has the data structure for an appointment queue.
    Cat
    The Class Cat will extend the animal class and is responsible for holding information that is specific to cats and not any other animal that might be within the rescue.
    Date
    The Class Date is responsible for everything related to time keeping and checking if the date is a valid date.
    Dog
    The Class Dog will extend the animal class and is responsible for holding information that is specific to dogs and not any other animal that might be within the rescue.
    Dog.Breed
    The Enum Breed.
    NoSuchListElementException
    The Class NoSuchListElementException extends an Exception and is thrown in another class to show that an element that is being searched for does not exist in the given list.
    Note
    The Class Note that has a date and other information for the purpose of recording information and allowing it to follow a specific object.
    PackDoptionGUI
    PackDoption GUI
    PackDoptionManager
    The purpose of the PackDoptionManager class is to interact with the GUI of the program and provide the information that is necessary for the user to see.
    PackDoptionReader
    The Class PackDoptionReader that is responsible for reading in a RescueList full of the individual rescues from a particular file.
    PackDoptionWriter
    The purpose of the PackDoptionWriter class is to be able to save all of the information held within the program to a file.
    Queue<E>
    This interface is a subset of the java.util.Queue interface.
    Rescue
    The Class Rescue is responsible for holding all information about a rescue that is used throughout the program.
    RescueList
    The Class RescueList is responsible for holding a SortedLinkedList of all the current rescues that are held within the system and has methods that allow for a rescue to be added, retrieved for use somewhere else and finally returns the total number of rescues that are in the list.
    SimpleListIterator<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
    Represents a cursor into a list that can move forward.
    SortedLinkedList<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
    The Class SortedLinkedList is a custom linked list that used nodes and an iterator to easily move through the list.
    SortedLinkedList.Node<E>
    The Class Node that holds a single value and is used in a chain to create a linked list.
    SortedList<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
    This interface is a subset of the java.util.List interface and requires that elements be stored in sorted order based on Comparable.
